ap. It is an opportunity gap."}),u.jsxs("div",{className:"space-y-5 text-lg text-[#2E3F4D] leading-relaxed mb-12",children:[u.jsx("p",{children:"Right now, in classrooms across Uganda and Zimbabwe, children sit shoulder to shoulder in overcrowded rooms with no access to a single computer, no library, and no internet connection. While their peers in other parts of the world learn to code, research, and collaborate online, these students are left behind before they even begin."}),u.jsx("p",{children:"Without digital literacy, young people cannot access the jobs, education, and opportunities that define modern life. The consequences ripple across generations: poverty deepens, inequality widens, and potential goes unrealised."}),u.jsx("p",{children:"This is the reality for millions of children in sub-Saharan Africa. But it does not have to stay that way."})]}),u.jsx(Mg,{})]}),u.jsx("div",{className:"lg:sticky lg:top-28",children:u.jsx("div",{className:"rounded-3xl overflow-hidden shadow-2xl",children:u.jsx("img",{src:"https://static.wixstatic.com/media/a7af79_e1c02a1ffefa4065b726989f317bb22b~mv2.jpg",alt:"Children in an under-resourced classroom in Africa",className:"w-full h-[520px] object-cover"})})})]})})}),u.jsx("section",{id:"our-promise",className:"py-24 lg:py-32 bg-[#EDF4F8]",children:u.jsxs("div",{className:"max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 text-center",children:[u.jsx("p",{className:"text-[#0891b2] font-medium uppercase tracking-widest text-sm mb-4",children:"Our Promise"}),u.jsx("h2",{className:"font-serif lg:text-5xl font-bold text-[#1E2D3A] mb-10 text-[33px]",children:"Every Child Deserves a Digital Future"}),u.jsx("blockquote",{className:"font-serif text-xl lg:text-2xl text-[#2E3F4D] italic leading-relaxed border-l-4 border-[#C4553A] pl-8 text-left mb-12 max-w-3xl mx-auto",children:"We exist to make it simple and transparent for anyone to sponsor digital literacy, library resources, and internet access for students in Uganda and Zimbabwe, so every child can reach the opportunities they deserve."}),u.jsxs("div",{className:"space-y-6 text-lg text-[#2E3F4D] leading-relaxed mb-12 max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center",children:[u.jsx("p",{children:"LeNoir Foundation believes that access to technology is not a luxury; it is a right. We partner with communities to build libraries, equip schools with IT infrastructure, and deliver digital skills training that transforms classrooms into launchpads for the future."}),u.jsx("p",{children:"Our promise is not just to provide equipment. It is to build ecosystems where education, community ownership, and digital innovation come together to break the cycle of inequality."})]}),u.jsx(te,{to:"/donate",className:"inline-block bg-[#C4553A] hover:bg-[#A8432A] text-white px-10 py-4 rounded-full font-medium transition-colors text-lg shadow-lg",children:"Support Our Mission"})]})}),u.jsx("section",{id:"our-story",className:"py-24 lg:py-32 bg-white",children:u.jsx("div",{className:"max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6",children:u.jsxs("div",{className:"grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-16 items-center",children:[u.jsxs("div",{className:"relative",children:[u.jsx("div",{className:"absolute -inset-4 bg-[#C8D5E0] rounded-t-full rounded-b-3xl transform -rotate-3"}),u.jsx("img",{src:"https://static.wixstatic.com/media/a7af79_5bae048c0a704778bf2dcd12cb3bb98b~mv2.jpg",alt:"James Jay Mawaka, Founder of LeNoir Foundation",className:"relative z-10 w-full h-[600px] object-cover rounded-t-full rounded-b-3xl shadow-xl"})]}),u.jsxs("div",{className:"text-center",children:[u.jsx("p",{className:"text-[#C4553A] font-medium uppercase tracking-widest text-sm mb-4",children:"Our Story"}),u.jsx("h2",{className:"font-serif lg:text-5xl font-bold text-[#1E2D3A] mb-8 text-[22px] text-center",children:"It Started With One Computer and a Neighbourhood Full of Friends Who Had Never Seen One"}),u.jsxs("div",{className:"space-y-5 text-lg text-[#2E3F4D] leading-relaxed mb-10",children:[u.jsx("p",{children:"When James Jay Mawaka was 10 years old, his mother bought him a desktop computer. It was a generous, life-changing gift. But it came with a weight he did not expect."}),u.jsx("p",{children:"James was the only child in his neighbourhood who had ever touched a computer. While he explored games, discovered new worlds on screen, and began to understand what technology could unlock, his friends lived in a different reality entirely. Resources were scarce. A computer was not just unaffordable; it was unimaginable. They had never seen one, let alone used one."}),u.jsx("p",{children:"What troubled James most was not the gap in access. It was the loneliness of it. He could not share what he was learning. He could not talk about the games he was playing or the things he was discovering. The excitement had nowhere to go, because the people he cared about most had no frame of reference for any of it. That feeling stayed with him."}),u.jsx("p",{children:"Years later, after studying at London South Bank University and Social Entrepreneurship at the University of Oxford, James Jay Mawaka turned that childhood frustration into a lifelong mission. In 2016, he founded LeNoir Foundation with a simple but powerful belief: no child should have to experience opportunity alone. If one child in a community gains access to technology, every child should."})]}),u.jsx("p",{className:"font-serif text-2xl lg:text-3xl font-bold text-[#C4553A] leading-snug border-l-4 border-[#C4553A] pl-6",children:'"Technology only matters when it is shared."'})]})]})})}),u.jsx("section",{id:"typespark",className:"py-24 lg:py-32 bg-[#FBF3DC]",children:u.jsx("div",{className:"max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6",children:u.jsxs("div",{className:"grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-16 items-start",children:[u.jsxs("div",{className:"text-center",children:[u.jsx("p",{className:"text-[#0891b2] font-medium uppercase tracking-widest text-sm mb-4 text-center",children:"Our Flagship Initiative"}),u.jsx("h2",{className:"font-serif lg:text-5xl font-bold text-[#1E2D3A] mb-4 text-center text-[28px]",children:"Meet TypeSpark: Free Typing Lessons for Every Child"}),u.jsx("p",{className:"text-[#2E3F4D] font-semibold text-lg mb-8",children:"24 lessons. 7 African languages. Works without the internet. Built by LeNoir Foundation."}),u.jsxs("div",{className:"space-y-5 text-base text-[#2E3F4D] leading-relaxed mb-10",children:[u.jsx("p",{children:"Most children in the communities we serve have never touched a keyboard. Before they can learn to code, research, or create, they need to learn the most fundamental digital skill of all: typing."}),u.jsx("p",{children:"TypeSpark is our answer. A free, offline-first typing tutor built specifically for children aged 6 to 16. It uses the Byte Back methodology — the same structured approach used in schools across Africa and the UK  to guide learners from their first keystrokes on the home row to full keyboard mastery across 24 lessons and 7 stages."}),u.jsx("p",{children:"What makes TypeSpark different is that it was designed for the realities of African classrooms: it works completely without an internet connection, stores all data locally on the device, and is available in English, Swahili, Shona, isiZulu, Luganda, isiNdebele, and Twi. A friendly hippo mascot named Kiboko, 21 achievement badges, daily challenges, and leaderboards keep children motivated and coming back. Schools can adopt the full platform for just $30 per year, giving up to 30 students access to every feature."})]}),u.jsx("div",{className:"grid grid-cols-3 gap-3 mb-10",children:[{icon:"✅",title:"100% Free",desc:"All lessons & features, always"},{icon:"📡",title:"Works Offline",desc:"Progressive Web App"},{icon:"🌍",title:"7 Languages",desc:"Swahili, Shona, isiZulu & more"},{icon:"📚",title:"24 Lessons",desc:"7 stages from home row to mastery"},{icon:"🛡️",title:"Child-Safe",desc:"No ads, no trackers, no chat"},{icon:"🏆",title:"Gamified",desc:"21 badges, daily challenges"}].map(d=>u.jsxs("div",{className:"bg-white/70 border border-[#E0C84A]/50 rounded-2xl p-3 text-center 